
ERROR HANDLING
______________


try :
used to test risky code


catch :
handles errors safely
prevents app crash


finally :
always runs
mostly used for cleanup


try/catch flow:

try {
   risky code
}

catch(error) {
   handle error
}

finally {
   always runs
}



error object contains:

error.message
error.name
error.stack



use cases:

API calls
database errors
invalid JSON
authentication
file handling



one line memory:

try     → test code
catch   → handle error
finally → always execute